benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Default behavior, individual filters (accountId, queueName, serviceName), date range, boolean flags toggled, and combined filters are exercised (TC01–TC10, TC23–TC24).
Empty Response: Covered via no data in system and filters matching no entries (TC11, TC29).

Query Parameters: Broad coverage of valid/invalid inputs, including malformed UUID, nonexistent account, malformed dates, extremes, and unexpected params; also security-focused inputs (TC12–TC14, TC17, TC24–TC26).
Authorization: Unauthorized access is validated with 401 (TC15).
Error Handling/Resilience: 500, 503, 504, transient network recovery, and performance/concurrency explored (TC16, TC18–TC20, TC27, TC30).
Content Type: Confirms application/octet-stream on success at least once (TC01).
gaps: Pagination: No tests for pagination parameters or multi-page behavior; large dataset test expects all entries returned, which may contradict expected pagination.
Caching Behavior: No verification of ETag/Last-Modified, Cache-Control, or conditional GET (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since) including 304 Not Modified.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios to validate throttling, 429 Too Many Requests, or Retry-After headers.
Authorization Depth: No 403 Forbidden for insufficient privileges/non-admin, no coverage of expired/insufficient-scope tokens.
Content Negotiation: No tests for Accept header handling for application/octet-stream or 406 when unacceptable media types are requested.

Query Parameter Edge Cases: Missing cases for minDate without maxDate, maxDate without minDate, minDate > maxDate (expect 400), timezone/ISO-8601 with time, inclusive/exclusive date boundary behavior, invalid boolean values (e.g., withHistory=maybe/1/0), repeated parameters, case sensitivity and URL-encoding nuances for queueName/serviceName.
Response Headers Consistency: Content-Type asserted only in TC01; no checks for Content-Length, consistent error JSON schema across 4xx/5xx, or charset where applicable.
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios: limit/offset (or API-specific paging), next/prev links or headers, and verify deterministic ordering across pages, especially with large datasets.
Add caching scenarios: verify Cache-Control and ETag/Last-Modified on responses; perform conditional GETs to assert 304 Not Modified and correct validators.
Introduce rate-limiting tests: burst requests to trigger 429 with proper Retry-After and ensure normal behavior resumes after cool-down.
Expand authorization coverage: test 403 for non-admin/insufficient permissions, expired token, and token scope enforcement.
Test content negotiation: requests with Accept headers for application/octet-stream, unsupported types to assert 406, and ensure Content-Type is consistent for all successful responses.

Cover parameter edge cases: minDate-only, maxDate-only, minDate > maxDate (expect 400), timezone-aware ISO-8601, date boundary inclusivity, invalid boolean values, duplicated params handling, case sensitivity and URL-encoding for names.
Verify headers consistently: assert Content-Type for all successful cases, Content-Length where applicable, and consistent JSON error schema for 4xx/5xx responses.

If API intentionally streams without pagination, document this behavior and adapt TC18 to assert streaming characteristics (memory/throughput) rather than expecting all entries in one response by default.
Add an explicit test for withHistory=true (and other flags=true) to confirm parity with default behavior.
